transcripts.transcript: President Trump and Joe Biden have brought their bitter campaign to an end. They spent the final day rallying support in states crucial to deciding the outcome. Almost 100 million Americans have already voted. Biden is seen to have the upper hand with leads in national and most swing state polls. President Trump's counting on heavy turnout by his supporters today, a federal appeals court has denied a request by Texas Republicans to ban drive through voting today in the state's most populous county. Republicans said they wanted to prevent election violations. The court denied the request without an explanation. Reported coronavirus cases have hit an all time high in the US on hospitalizations have risen in 44 states. Battleground states in the elections are facing their worst moments off the pandemic. Wisconsin posted America's third highest cases per capita in the past week. Seven day average cases are at record in Michigan and Iowa on Hurricane Eater has strengthened into one of the Atlantic most powerful storms of the year. It's warring towards Central America, with winds of 150 miles an hour. The Category four storm is expected to cause flash floods and life threatening storm surges when it slams into Nicaragua today.
